# PERSONA OS BINDING ORDER RULE
# ============================================================

status: canonical
layer: meta
domain: binding-order
system: persona-os
owner: Boss
prepared_by: Zero

purpose:
Defines the fixed chapter order
for PersonaOS integrated binding output.

# ============================================================
# 1. FIXED LAYER ORDER
# ============================================================

The binding order must follow:

010.constitution
020.architecture
030.model
040.runtime
050.flow
060.integration
070.operations
080.policy
090.interface
100.security
110.infrastructure
120.implementation
130.development

# ============================================================
# 2. FIXED DOMAIN ORDER
# ============================================================

Within each layer, the fixed domain order must be:

010.core
020.identity
030.state
040.memory
050.growth
060.builder
070.visual
080.runtime-hosting
090.snapshot
100.package
110.distribution
120.external-rights
130.access-license-transfer
140.integration
150.security
160.governance
170.operations-support

# ============================================================
# 3. FILE ORDER INSIDE EACH DOMAIN
# ============================================================

Inside each domain folder, files must be ordered by filename sort.

Rule:
- index first if present
- overview second if present
- remaining files in filename sort order

# ============================================================
# 4. BINDING INCLUSION RULE
# ============================================================

The integrated binding output must include:

- top-level layer overview/index files
- domain index files
- domain overview files
- domain canonical files

The integrated binding output must exclude:

- 999.archive
- 999.dump
- temporary files
- *.moved.bak
- ad hoc review outputs unless explicitly requested

# ============================================================
# 5. META INCLUSION RULE
# ============================================================

920.meta files are not included by default in the main canonical binding.

Exception:
Meta files may be included only when creating:
- review bundle
- migration bundle
- design map bundle

# ============================================================
# 6. OFFICIAL CANONICAL BINDING PATH
# ============================================================

The main canonical integrated reading path is:

010.constitution -> 020.architecture -> 030.model -> 040.runtime -> 050.flow -> 060.integration -> 070.operations -> 080.policy -> 090.interface -> 100.security -> 110.infrastructure -> 120.implementation -> 130.development

# ============================================================
# 7. STABILITY RULE
# ============================================================

Once a binding order is fixed,
new documents must be inserted by layer and domain,
not by ad hoc narrative order.

If a new file cannot be placed clearly,
the design is incomplete and must be reviewed first.
